<div class='wrapper'>
  <h1>Your account</h1>
  <p>
    This is your account number. Use it to log in to Freshreader. Store it somewhere safe.<br>
  </p>

  <code class="account-number">
    <%= @user.pretty_account_number %>
  </code>

  <p>
    That's right. No username, no password. Simple as that.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>How to save content</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Using the bookmarkletâ€”drag this link to your bookmarks bar: <a style="font-weight: bold" onclick="return false;" class="internal-link" href="javascript:location.href='https://freshreader.app/save?url='+encodeURIComponent(location.href)">Save to Freshreader</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      Using the Android app (beta): download the .apk file to get started saving content to your list! <a style="font-weight: bold" class="internal-link" href="/apks/freshreader-v1.0.0.apk">Download Android app (freshreader-v1.0.0.apk)</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Now that you know how to save content, let's open your reading list:
    <%= link_to "View saved items", '/articles', class: "internal-link", style: "font-weight: bold;" %>
  </p>

  <hr>

  <div>
    <h2>Danger zone</h2>
    <p>
      Not interested in Freshreader anymore? That's okay, we're glad you were here for a while. Be excellent, and keep learning every day. :)
    </p>
    <%= button_to 'Delete account', :account, method: :delete, class: 'btn-danger internal-link', onclick: "return confirm('Are you sure you want to delete your Freshreader account?');"%>
  </div>
</div>
